🔹 Step 1: Start the program

🔹 Step 2: Initialize variables
Set head = NULL (Contacts)
Set front = rear = -1 (Message Queue)
Set top = -1 (Call Stack)

🔹 Step 3: Display Menu
Add Contact
View Contacts
Send Message
View Messages
Delete Message
Make Call
Call History
Delete Last Call
Exit

🔹 Step 4: Read user choice

🔹 Step 5: Perform operation using switch-case
--➤ Case 1: Add Contact
Input name and number
Create new node
Insert at beginning of linked list
--➤ Case 2: View Contacts
Traverse linked list
Display all contacts
--➤ Case 3: Send Message
Input message
Check if queue is full
Insert message into queue (rear++)
--➤ Case 4: View Messages
Check if queue is empty
Display messages from front to rear
--➤ Case 5: Delete Message
Check if queue is empty
Remove message from front (front++)
--➤ Case 6: Make Call
Input contact name
Push name into stack (top++)
--➤ Case 7: Call History
Check if stack is empty
Display calls from top to bottom
--➤ Case 8: Delete Last Call
Check if stack is empty
Pop last call (top--)
--➤ Case 9: Exit
Exit loop
--➤ Default
Display "Invalid Choice"

🔹 Step 6: Repeat Steps 3–5 until user selects Exit

🔹 Step 7: Free memory
Delete all nodes in linked list

🔹 Step 8: Stop the program
